    <note>Lu(9) Yirou [16389] A Huating man, who was registered (guan) in Kaifeng. See documentation for probable uncle (or father), Quan [16387], and father-in-law, Zhou(1) Zhidao [483]. It seems likely that immigrants to Kaifeng (&amp; Luoyang) from the same region may have lived in separate sections of the capitals and continued to intermarry with each other. CHECK. Jiangnan TZ, 119.38a; Yunjian zhi, 'zhong,' 26a. CBD, 2, 1210.</note>
